main event: Unidentified flying object sightings reported near Goose Air Force Base, Labrador, on May 25 and May 6, 1953.
interesting points: A pilot reported an unidentified object traveling at tremendous speed, estimated at over 1,000 mph., An unidentified object was described as round, dark in color, and about the size of a DC-6., Multiple sightings occurred over a few days, with some objects observed for 10 minutes., No sound was associated with the sightings, and no radar contact could be established., The incident was part of Project Blue Book investigations into UFOs in the 1950s.
sighted object: luminous object and another round, dark object
witness description: Pilots and air traffic controllers at Goose AFB
